FT  29 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Scottish Inv Trust net assets improve
The net asset value per share of the Scottish Investment Trust showed a
modest improvement to 208.3p at the six months ended April 30, against
198.5p a year earlier and 206.2p at the October year end.
Gross income, including underwriting commission of Pounds 82,000 (Pounds
77,000), rose by 10.4 per cent, from Pounds 9.74m to Pounds 10.75m. Earnings
per share came out at 1.83p (1.56p) and the interim dividend is raised to
1.6p (1.5p).
